  "text": "We employed a recently developed bioinformatic workflow [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] to filter, interpret and call alleles out of the raw sequences. Raw reads were initially quality-checked by removing royalsocietypublishing.org/journal/rspb Proc. R. Soc. B 285: 20182426 low-quality reads ( phred quality score ! 30 in at least 90% of bases) and reads with any sequencing errors on primers or barcodes. The final allele calling of each sample allowed only variants that passed our conservative approach and had been identified in both replicates (i.e. originated from independent PCRs). All other steps on the bioinformatic pipeline were performed as described elsewhere [CITATION_3] .",
